laboratory_examinations.findings: The absence of an aortic knuckle on the left side of the mediastinum; right border of the descending thoracic aorta noted on the right side of the spine.
Right vertebral artery was prominent with high-velocity, low-resistance flow; left vertebral artery showed flow reversal with a high-resistance waveform.

Right-sided aorta giving three branches; left subclavian artery not visualized; communication with a small-caliber left vertebral artery; patchy area of consolidation in the medial basal segment of the right lower lobe.
Absence of flow-related enhancement in the left vertebral artery initially; flow enhancement noted in the left vertebral artery upon repeating TOF-MRA.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Initial absence of flow-related enhancement followed by noted flow enhancement.
